div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 17:05:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/from-playboy-cricketer-to-populist-politician-how-imran-khan-promises-to-pakistan-fell-by-the-wayside" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/06/good-posture-back-pain-how-to-avoid" target="_blank">Is good posture overrated? Back to first principles on back pain - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> For ages, bad posture has been assumed to cause back pain. Now physiotherapists are rethinking what we should be doing with our spines. People with back pain tend to have weak muscles in their backs, leaving their spines vulnerable. Get the postural muscles strong and you could cure the back pain, they are told.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 20:00:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/06/good-posture-back-pain-how-to-avoid" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/06/is-germanys-great-economy-sinking-into-slowcession" target="_blank">Is Germany’s great economy sinking into ‘slowcession’? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Recent figures have indicated that the good times have come to an end, with Europe’s largest economy stuck in recession. Key data this week will offer a hint as to whether the eurozone's powerhouse can shake off recent stagnation. Germany's economy has been described as industrial powerhouse and export world champion.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 23:05:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/06/is-germanys-great-economy-sinking-into-slowcession" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/aug/06/sydney-gangland-shooting-killing-gun-violence-crime-criminal-cocaine-drug-bondi-marrickville-greenacre-alen-moradian" target="_blank">Daylight shootings and a vast ‘labour force of organised crime’: the challenge of ending Sydney’s gangland war - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Alen Moradian was instructing his minions to bury $2.7m in a suburban vegetable garden. The cocaine trafficker feared police were on to him, and wanted to hide the cash. He was soon charged with drug offences for which he was jailed for a minimum of 10 years.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 20:00:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/aug/06/sydney-gangland-shooting-killing-gun-violence-crime-criminal-cocaine-drug-bondi-marrickville-greenacre-alen-moradian" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/gallery/2023/aug/05/edinburgh-festival-2023-kicks-off-murdo-macleod-in-pictures" target="_blank">Let’s start the show: Edinburgh festival 2023 kicks off – in pictures - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Photographer Murdo MacLeod presents his view of the opening week’s Edinburgh festival and fringe shows. From a show for one to a giant dinner party, the festival has been transformed into a party for one. Murdo's view of opening week's fringe shows is his view from behind the scenes.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 16:09:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/gallery/2023/aug/05/edinburgh-festival-2023-kicks-off-murdo-macleod-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/05/my-boat-was-attacked-by-orcas-too-what-does-this-say-about-the-sea" target="_blank">Orcas ‘attacked’ my boat too. What does this say about the sea? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Violent interactions with humans off the Iberian coast have caused alarm but mystery still surrounds the apex predators. Two pods of orca preying on sperm whale calves were defeated by adult whales who had gathered around to defend their young. The orcas then turned their attention to our 6m fishing boat, circling us, before ramming our prow. Five of the orcas swam directly at our side, creating a compression wave as if to tip us over.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:33:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/05/my-boat-was-attacked-by-orcas-too-what-does-this-say-about-the-sea" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/05/comedians-worst-edinburgh-ed-byrne-grace-campbell-john-robins-olga-koch-paul-sinha" target="_blank">‘I almost died. Just kidding! I only broke my leg’: comedians share their Edinburgh fringe horror stories - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The fringe can take its toll, but it’s all good material, right? Ed Byrne, Paul Sinha, Olga Koch et al have lived to tell the tale. One night I had my first encounter with Buckfast and got to sleep at 7am. Another day I had to be up at 10am to flyer our show.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 10:55:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/05/comedians-worst-edinburgh-ed-byrne-grace-campbell-john-robins-olga-koch-paul-sinha" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/its-more-february-than-august-holidaymakers-sit-out-storm-in-cornwall" target="_blank">‘It’s more February than August’: holidaymakers sit out storm in Cornwall - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Britain’s soggy summer is enough to make you give up and head to the Med. Yet families are happily splashing around on the beach in St Ives, Cornwall. Kate and Tilly Perrett look as if they might be regretting taking their summer holiday in Cornwall.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 15:10:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/its-more-february-than-august-holidaymakers-sit-out-storm-in-cornwall" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/05/england-nigeria-defence-press-tactical-preview-womens-world-cup" target="_blank">England's fluid back three and high press can keep Nigeria threat at bay | Anita Asante - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Nigeria are one of seven teams to have qualified for all nine Women’s World Cups. The Super Falcons have never progressed beyond the quarter-finals. They beat Australia 3-2 and drew 0-0 with Canada in their last-16 clash. Randy Waldrum's side are likely to underestimate the Super Falcons against England.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 17:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/05/england-nigeria-defence-press-tactical-preview-womens-world-cup" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/japan-norway-womens-world-cup-last-16-report" target="_blank">Japan advance to World Cup last eight as Hinata Miyazawa strike sinks Norway - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Japan beat Norway 3-1 to reach the quarter-finals of the Women’s World Cup in Wellington. Risa Shimizu and Hinata Miyazawa scored second-half goals for the Japanese. Guro Reiten had levelled for Norway in the first half, heading home after an own goal from Ingrid Engen.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 10:21:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/japan-norway-womens-world-cup-last-16-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/uswnt-sweden-world-cup-knockout-stage-preview" target="_blank">Struggling USA out for World Cup reset against familiar foes Sweden - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Sweden and the United States have met in six of the past eight World Cups, but never in the knockout rounds. The U.S. women hope to avoid the worst finish in program history. The United States women also don't look anything like a team playing well enough to win a World Cup.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:39:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/uswnt-sweden-world-cup-knockout-stage-preview" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/great-danes-vow-to-give-no-quarter-in-world-cup-showdown-with-matildas" target="_blank">Great Danes vow to give no quarter in World Cup showdown with Matildas - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The Danish team arrived in Australia for the Women’s World Cup, they set up camp in Perth. It was a great place to prepare for the tournament, with warm weather akin to the Danish summer. The players were particularly touched when some young footballers from Denmark, Western Australia, travelled five hours to greet the team at their pre-World Cup training.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 20:00:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/great-danes-vow-to-give-no-quarter-in-world-cup-showdown-with-matildas" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/steve-borthwick-rues-englands-missed-opportunities-in-defeat-by-wales" target="_blank">Steve Borthwick rues England’s ‘missed opportunities’ in defeat by Wales - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> England coach Steve Borthwick insists his side will bounce back against Wales at Twickenham next Saturday. ‘The team will start to sharpen up over the next few weeks as we play the next three games. Every one of these experiences will be positive for us as we build towards the World Cup,’ says head coach. Wales coach Gatland says English forwards were blowing before half-time.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 21:06:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/steve-borthwick-rues-englands-missed-opportunities-in-defeat-by-wales" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/manchester-city-pep-guardiola-too-many-games-trophy-success" target="_blank">‘It’s getting worse’: Manchester City have too many games, says Guardiola - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Pep Guardiola unhappy last year’s success has resulted in busy schedule. City kick off the season on Sunday in the Community Shield against Arsenal. After their game against Burnley they will face Burnley on Friday night before travelling to Athens for the European Super Cup against Sevilla.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 21:30:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/05/manchester-city-pep-guardiola-too-many-games-trophy-success" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/boxing-dillian-whyte-returns-adverse-test-anthony-joshua-rematch-off" target="_blank">Dillian Whyte vows to prove innocence over ‘adverse’ test with Joshua fight off - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Dillian Whyte returned ‘adverse analytical findings’ in anti-doping test. Boxer insists he is ‘completely innocent’ as rematch cancelled. Anthony Joshua could still fight at London’s O2 Arena as Matchroom seek late replacement opponent.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 12:27:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/boxing-dillian-whyte-returns-adverse-test-anthony-joshua-rematch-off" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/england-new-zealand-netball-world-cup-semi-final-report" target="_blank">England outlast New Zealand to reach Netball World Cup final for first time - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> England reach Netball World Cup final for first time after beating New Zealand 46-40 in semi-final. Roses will face Australia in their first final at the tournament in Cape Town. Jess Thirlby’s team went toe-to-toe with the Silver Ferns in an unrelenting contest.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 10:58:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/england-new-zealand-netball-world-cup-semi-final-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/05/cherish-the-championship-its-competitive-nature-offers-football-as-it-should-be" target="_blank">Cherish the Championship, its level playing field offers football as it should be | Jonathan Wilson - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> League is packed with clubs recalling past glories and desperate to escape it but success shouldn't just be for the moneyed elite. Of the 24 sides in the Championship, only Plymouth and Rotherham have never won the league or reached a domestic cup final. The 2.Bundesliga has its share of fallen giants but nowhere else is the spread of honours so great.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 19:00:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/05/cherish-the-championship-its-competitive-nature-offers-football-as-it-should-be" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/scotland-france-rugby-world-cup-warmup-report" target="_blank">Scotland roar back in the second half to stun France despite Fagerson red card - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Graham, Schoeman and Cherry tries overturn 21-3 deficit. Scotland claw back an 18-point deficit after half-time. Fabien Galthié's largely second-choice XV scored three tries through a classic blend of precision, speed and power. France were so good for 40 minutes, it was difficult to say if Scotland had been that bad.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 16:39:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/scotland-france-rugby-world-cup-warmup-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/ireland-italy-rugby-world-cup-warmup-report" target="_blank">Doris in form as Ireland complete comfortable win over Italy - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Six Nations champions run in five tries in World Cup warm-up win over Italy. Caelan Doris shone and Jack Conan suffered an injury scare. Back-rower Conan departed the field shortly before half-time and was later pictured in a protective boot on the bench.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 21:32:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/ireland-italy-rugby-world-cup-warmup-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/charlie-hatton-defies-conditions-to-win-mens-mountain-bike-downhill" target="_blank">Katie Archibald honours late partner with pursuit gold for Britain in Glasgow - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Archibald, Barker, Knight and Morris beat New Zealand in the gold medal race. Scotland’s partner, Rab Wardell, died of a cardiac arrest in bed last August. It was also a vindication of her decision to overcome her grief and continue racing.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 22:44:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/charlie-hatton-defies-conditions-to-win-mens-mountain-bike-downhill" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/05/social-jetlag-sleep-deprivation-plaguing-society" target="_blank">‘Social jetlag’: why a good night’s sleep is now a luxury that many go without | Sonia Sodha - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Sleep deprivation leads to ill-health but our 24/7 society is inflicting it on more and more of us. A night spent tossing and turning leaves me headachey and prone to brain fog. Research shows that sleep is no less fundamental to physical and mental wellbeing than diet and exercise.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 17:03:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/05/social-jetlag-sleep-deprivation-plaguing-society" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/05/donald-trump-has-the-republican-party-tied-up-in-knots-cartoon" target="_blank">Donald Trump has the Republican party tied up in knots – cartoon - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The former president protests his innocence – and his followers believe him. The cartoon shows that the former president is not guilty of any wrongdoing. He is accused of the murder of former US President Richard Nixon in the 1980s and 1990s. Nixon's supporters believe him to be innocent, but his supporters do not.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 17:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/05/donald-trump-has-the-republican-party-tied-up-in-knots-cartoon" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/05/the-mail-is-stuck-in-the-past-its-sneering-woke-list-is-actually-a-badge-of-honour" target="_blank">Appearing on the Mail’s sneering ‘Woke List’ is actually a badge of honour | Kathryn Bromwich - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Justin Welby and Emily Maitlis are simply guilty of pointing out the destruction of the planet or having empathy with others. The Mail on Sunday's 'Woke List' includes the usual susp