ury" target="_blank">At home with Tyson Fury: ‘I do the bins, I do the school run and I love picking up the dog poo’ - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> At Home With the Furys is a nine-part fly-on-the-wall reality series due to hit Netflix later this month. The heavyweight champion talks marriage, mental health and why he’s invited the cameras in to make the show. Fury: 'I’m sorry about all this,” Paris will occasionally say, but the truth is that she's got the chaos under control.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 06:00:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/05/at-home-with-tyson-fury" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/05/i-cried-with-anger-the-trials-and-torment-when-travelling-with-blindness" target="_blank">‘I cried with anger’: the trials and torment when travelling with blindness - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> A train guard accused me of faking blindness when I was travelling from Cambridge to London. Society needs to be educated about the nuances of sight loss. There were extensive apologies, and I went home and cried. With anger. The train guard apologised for his actions, but I lost my temper and put out my false eye.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/05/i-cried-with-anger-the-trials-and-torment-when-travelling-with-blindness" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/one-of-last-photos-of-queen-elizabeth-ii-up-for-national-award" target="_blank">One of last photos of Queen Elizabeth II up for national award - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> People invited to choose from 20 images taken in 2022 for the UK Picture Editors’ Guild Awards. People can choose from photos taken between 1 January and 31 December 2022 for photo of the year at the annual awards. One of the last public pictures of the late Queen Elizabeth II is up for an award.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 06:00:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/one-of-last-photos-of-queen-elizabeth-ii-up-for-national-award" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/wildlife-lovers-fear-for-nature-reserve-threatened-by-cambridge-university-building" target="_blank">Wildlife lovers fear for nature reserve threatened by Cambridge university building - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Paradise nature reserve on the banks of the river Cam is home to eight species of bat, including the rare and endangered barbastelle. The tiny 2.2 hectare reserve protects the river corridor between Cambridge city centre and Grantchester Meadows. It has been popular with Cambridge students, college dons and nature-lovers for centuries.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 10:45:31 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/05/wildlife-lovers-fear-for-nature-reserve-threatened-by-cambridge-university-building" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/donald-trump-threatening-social-media-post-flagged-by-prosecutors-in-court-filing" target="_blank">Donald Trump: threatening social media post flagged by prosecutors in court filing - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Prosecutors have asked ex-president be banned from sharing evidence with unauthorized people after post on Truth Social. Trump spokesperson said post was the ‘definition of political speech’ protected by the constitution’s first amendment and that it did not have to do with the criminal case.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 16:35:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/donald-trump-threatening-social-media-post-flagged-by-prosecutors-in-court-filing" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/west-african-bloc-gives-niger-coup-leaders-until-sunday-to-end-revolt" target="_blank">West African bloc prepares for military action as Niger coup deadline looms - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Defence chiefs deliver ultimatum for Sunday after mediation fails to reinstate elected president. Economic Community of West African States (Ecowas) gives Niger’s coup leaders until Sunday to step down and reinstate the elected president, Mohamed Bazoum. The crisis threatens regional security and has drawn in global powers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 10:57:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/west-african-bloc-gives-niger-coup-leaders-until-sunday-to-end-revolt" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/flu-shot-cheerleader-desiree-jennings-interview" target="_blank">‘Flu shot cheerleader’ speaks out on being used by anti-vaxxer movement - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Desiree Jennings spoke with NBC about being cast into US spotlight in 2009 after she went on video and expressed her belief that her seasonal flu shot led to an unexplainable disability involving erratic movements and slurred speech. Jennings said vaccine skeptics recruited her, sensationalized her story and ultimately discarded her after she was accused of being a fraud.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 20:04:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/flu-shot-cheerleader-desiree-jennings-interview" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/travis-king-us-declines-prisoner-of-war-norht-korea" target="_blank">US declines to classify soldier who entered North Korea as prisoner of war - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Travis King is detained in North Korea after crossing into the country last month. Decision could mean he is not covered by the protections entitled to prisoners of war under Geneva conventions. Decision is highly sensitive for US military given commitment to leave no soldier behind enemy lines. King could not be classified as a prisoner of war because he crossed into North Korea.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:34:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/05/travis-king-us-declines-prisoner-of-war-norht-korea" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/texas-judge-rules-abortion-ban-too-strict-for-risky-pregnancies" target="_blank">Texas judge rules abortion ban too strict for risky pregnancies - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Ruling in Austin was the first to undercut the law since it took effect in 2022. State attorney general immediately appeals against ruling that says doctors must be allowed to end unsafe pregnancies. Ruling delivers a major victory to abortion rights supporters, who see the case as a potential blueprint to weaken restrictions elsewhere.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 08:49:12 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/texas-judge-rules-abortion-ban-too-strict-for-risky-pregnancies" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/04/lucky-border-terrier-makes-incredible-journey-100-miles-across-switzerland" target="_blank">Border terrier makes incredible journey 100 miles across Switzerland - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Lucky was left in kennels in Bern but escaped and made her way to Lake Geneva. The 14-year-old border terrier made an epic 100-mile journey across Switzerland on the eve of the country’s national holiday. Lucky was found and traced to owners and returned to her owners.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 18:53:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/04/lucky-border-terrier-makes-incredible-journey-100-miles-across-switzerland" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/04/mark-margolis-dead-breaking-bad-better-caul-saul" target="_blank">Breaking Bad actor Mark Margolis dies aged 83 - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Margolis played drug lord Hector Salamanca in Breaking Bad and Better Call Saul. He also appeared in Scarface and The Wrestler. Margolis died at Mount Sinai Hospital in New York City following a short illness. His wife, Jacqueline, and son, Morgan, were at his bedside.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 17:07:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/04/mark-margolis-dead-breaking-bad-better-caul-saul" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/kenya-police-haiti-human-rights-concerns" target="_blank">Kenya’s offer to send police to Haiti sparks human rights concerns - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Human rights groups say move could worsen country’s security crisis given police force's poor human rights record. Move welcomed by officials in the embattled Caribbean nation, but prompted concern among human rights groups who say it could worsen the country's security crisis. Prime minister Ariel Henry requested international support from the UN last year when gangs began taking control of much of the country.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 11:15:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/05/kenya-police-haiti-human-rights-concerns" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/05/a-year-on-the-devastating-long-term-effects-of-pakistans-floods-are-revealed" target="_blank">A year on, the devastating long-term effects of Pakistan’s floods are revealed - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Islamic Relief says rich nations must compensate those suffering worst of climate crisis. 40% of children in flood-affected areas had stunted growth and 25% were underweight. 80% of mothers reported sickness among children, with outbreaks of diarrhoea, malaria and dengue fever increasing.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 06:00:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/05/a-year-on-the-devastating-long-term-effects-of-pakistans-floods-are-revealed" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/05/heaven-review-traverse-edinburgh-eugene-obrien" target="_blank">Heaven review – the bittersweet taste of love - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Eugene O'Brien’s Heaven is set on the weekend of a spirited wedding in Edenderry in the Irish midlands. A fiftysomething couple find themselves reckoning with a romanticised past and an uninspiring present. A compellingly acted, exquisitely written play by Eugene O’Brien.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 16:02:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/05/heaven-review-traverse-edinburgh-eugene-obrien" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/05/the-kinks-former-keyboardist-john-gosling-dies-aged-75" target="_blank">The Kinks’ former keyboardist John Gosling dies aged 75 - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Members pay tribute to ‘great man’ who played with band in 1970s. Gosling joined the Kinks in 1970 as a keyboard player. Brothers Ray and Dave Davies formed the band in the 1960s, with Gosling joining in 1970. The Kinks have paid tribute to their former bandmate John Gosling.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 15:34:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/05/the-kinks-former-keyboardist-john-gosling-dies-aged-75" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/05/edinburgh-festival-fringe-acts-outraged-by-censorship-of-provocative-posters" target="_blank">Edinburgh festival fringe acts outraged by censorship of ‘provocative’ posters - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Performers and producers say arts are being ‘sanitised’ amid more sensitive attitudes towards swearing and sexual politics. As a result, some of the more provocative imagery printed by performers has already been censored or even defaced. Posters, including those displaying a lineup of bare buttocks, a large pair of breasts, a woman wearing cat paws and a drag queen children’s entertainer have all become embroiled in censorship rows.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 11:36:58 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/05/edinburgh-festival-fringe-acts-outraged-by-censorship-of-provocative-posters" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/05/a-bonkers-gig-how-heavy-metal-bands-are-helping-keep-uk-church-organs-alive" target="_blank">‘A bonkers gig’: how heavy metal bands are helping keep UK church organs alive - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Heavy metal bands Arð and Pantheïst performed at Huddersfield town hall accompanied by the organ. The Organic Doom gig was so successful that they plan to repeat the performance around the UK. The hope is that events like these will help save some of the nation’s pipe organs from destruction.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 15:11:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/05/a-bonkers-gig-how-heavy-metal-bands-are-helping-keep-uk-church-organs-alive" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/05/meg-2-the-trench-review-another-fin-mess-for-jason-statham" target="_blank">Meg 2: The Trench review – another fin mess for Jason Statham - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Ben Wheatley’s prehistoric shark sequel comes adrift in a surfeit of new lizardy threats, a clunking screenplay and a total lack of onscreen chemistry. The Meg 2 brazenly steals from other pictures and throws a bunch of extra creatures into the mix. Not only are multiple megalodons; there is a pack of ocean-dwelling fish-lizard-creatures so savage that they seem to have an extra set of teeth on their chins.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 13:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/05/meg-2-the-trench-review-another-fin-mess-for-jason-statham" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/04/georgie-grier-plays-to-sell-out-edinburgh-crowd-24-hours-after-tearful-tweet" target="_blank">Georgie Grier plays to sell-out Edinburgh crowd 24 hours after tearful tweet - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Georgie Grier received messages of support from comedians including Jason Manford and Dara Ó Briain. Actor and writer posted yesterday after performing her one-woman show Sunsets to one audience member. She said: “There was one person in my audience today when I performed my one-man play, ‘Sunsets’ at #edfringe. It’s fine, isn’t it?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 21:32:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/04/georgie-grier-plays-to-sell-out-edinburgh-crowd-24-hours-after-tearful-tweet" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/27/next-stop-spain-how-to-start-your-european-road-trip-on-the-sea" target="_blank">Next stop Spain: how to start your European road trip on the sea - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Katie Nicholson and Ciaran Nicholson have fallen in love with the comfort, ease and flexibility of ferry travel. The couple set sail with Brittany Ferries from the UK to Spain on a new adventure. They are remote working from Spain and Italy on and off for the rest of the year. Good food, great views and comfortable cabin make for a relaxing journey.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 27 Jun 2023 10:33:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/27/next-stop-spain-how-to-start-your-european-road-trip-on-the-sea" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/15/instaglamour-nerdy-planner-or-freewheeler-take-this-quiz-to-find-out-your-traveller-personality" target="_blank">Instaglamour, nerdy planner or freewheeler? Take this quiz to find out your traveller personality - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Take this quiz to discover what kind of traveller you really are. Some of us just can’t get enough of the likes and follows, while others can't wait to switch off and be at one with a destination. To find out more about hassle-free holidays with Brittany Ferries click here.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 15 Jun 2023 08:41:50 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/15/instaglamour-nerdy-planner-or-freewheeler-take-this-quiz-to-find-out-your-traveller-personality" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jul/04/wine-dine-and-relax-why-taking-the-ferry-is-the-ultimate-in-slow-travel" target="_blank">Wine, dine and relax: why taking the ferry is the ultimate in slow travel - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Take a ferry for your European getaway to avoid airport hassles. Enjoy great food on the way and arrive at your destination feeling fresh and ready to go. From the historic chateaux of the Loire valley to the sunshine glamour of the French Riviera, a holiday to France never fails to delight.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 09:30:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jul/04/wine-dine-and-relax-why-taking-the-ferry-is-the-ultimate-in-slow-travel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/15/driving-your-own-car-to-europe-dont-forget-to-take-these-10-essentials-with-you" target="_blank">Driving your own car to Europe? Don’t forget to take these 10 essentials with you - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Brittany Ferries are a great way to start your European holiday with a car. Here are 10 road trip essentials to check before you set off well prepared. Take your car on a Brittany ferries trip to Europe with award-winning service and plenty of space to relax.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 15 Jun 2023 08:42:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/15/driving-your-own-car-to-europe-dont-forget-to-take-these-10-essentials-with-you" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/06/the-moment-i-knew-we-hadnt-met-i-hadnt-seen-a-picture-but-when-i-read-her-words-a-humming-started-up" target="_blank">The moment I knew: we hadn’t met, I hadn’t seen a picture. But when I read her words a humming started up - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Berndt Sellheim fell in love with a mystery woman on a dating platform 16 years ago. After a flurry of communications, her profile on the platform vanished. Sellheim's now-wife wrote the words on her dating profile: 'Do you prefer Sartre over sport? Bukowski over beige?'</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 20:00:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/06/the-moment-i-knew-we-hadnt-met-i-hadnt-seen-a-picture-but-when-i-read-her-words-a-humming-started-up" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/arts-and-crafts-schoolhouse-renovation-in-kent-proves-a-class-act" target="_blank">An Arts and Crafts schoolhouse renovation in Kent proves a class act - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Bill and Hayley Kingston bought their atmospheric house in Kent in 2017. Originally an Arts and Crafts schoolhouse built in 1902, it was in a poor state of repair. Divided into two residential properties during the 1970s, its interior bore little resemblance to any original layout.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 15:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/arts-and-crafts-schoolhouse-renovation-in-kent-proves-a-class-act" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/this-is-how-we-do-it-were-expecting-another-baby-and-its-turbocharged-our-sex-life" target="_blank">This is how we do it: ‘We’re expecting another baby, and it’s turbocharged our sex life’ - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Olivia and Finlay had sex off the menu for a time after their first child. But their second pregnancy is making them horny – and creative – again. Olivia says: 'My libido is surging and I suddenly want it all the time, which is thrilling' As a parent, sex becomes like sleep: you get it when you can, Olivia says.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 11:00:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/this-is-how-we-do-it-were-expecting-another-baby-and-its-turbocharged-our-sex-life" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/how-i-made-friends-with-my-scammer" target="_blank">‘I didn’t trust him. But I was curious about him’: how I made friends with my scammer - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Comedian Michelle Brasier contacted the seller of an online purchase that never turned up. She had no idea it would be the start of an unlikely and troubling friendship. The Australian comedian spent a lot of time in her bathtub - a large clear storage tub in the bottom of her shower – eating bread and watching Buffy the Vampire Slayer.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 09:00:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/05/how-i-made-friends-with-my-scammer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/05/derek-guy-the-notorious-fashion-tweeter-on-sunaks-short-trousers" target="_blank">Derek Guy: the notorious fashion tweeter on Sunak’s short trousers - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> US menswear critic Derek Guy keeps a close eye on politicians and says ‘they all dress equally badly’ Images of Rishi Sunak's shrunken trousers flooded social media long before he boarded the plane. ‘I don’t think he has a grand theory for how short sleeves and pants make him look taller’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 08:00:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/05/derek-guy-the-notorious-fashion-tweeter-on-sunaks-short-trousers" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/05/roast-chicken-tomato-green-bean-salad-recipes-yotam-ottolenghi-alfresco-feast" target="_blank">Roast chicken and super salads: Yotam Ottolenghi’s recipes for an alfresco feast - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The secret to alfresco success is prep, so try this trio of make-ahead recipes for size. The apricot-basted chicken with preserved lemon, plus sides of tomato and chickpea, and green beans and aïoli is a hit.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 07:00:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/05/roast-chicken-tomato-green-bean-salad-recipes-yotam-ottolenghi-alfresco-feast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/01/bride-wades-through-floodwaters-after-philippines-hit-by-typhoons-video-report" target="_blank">Bride wades through floodwaters after Philippines hit by typhoons – video report - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The Philippines was hit with torrential rain over seven days, brought by Typhoon Doksuri and intensified by Typhoon Khanun. Low-lying villages to the north of the country were the worst affected. Residents were forced to travel by small wooden boats and roads were inundated.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 01 Aug 2023 12:10:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/01/bride-wades-through-floodwaters-after-philippines-hit-by-typhoons-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/31/wildfires-cross-us-border-into-canada-triggering-evacuation-order-video" target="_blank">Wildfires cross US border into Canada triggering evacuation order – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Canadian town of Osoyoos ordered to evacuate after wildfire crosses border from Washington state. Firefighters are using water cannon from planes to try to control the blaze, which is estimated to be 885 hectares (2,200 acres) in size. Local authorities estimate the blaze is 885-heater-size.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 31 Jul 2023 08:44:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/31/wildfires-cross-us-border-into-canada-triggering-evacuation-order-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/video/2023/jul/26/sinead-oconnor-the-turbulent-career-of-the-irish-sensation-video-obituary" target="_blank">The life and career of Sinéad O’Connor: ‘I was really a protest singer’ - video obituary - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Sinéad O'Connor has died at the age of 56, prompting grief and tributes. Irish singer abjured conventional stardom for most of her career. Some never forgave her for ripping up a picture of the pope on American TV. The Dubliner enjoyed something of a renaissance in recent years.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 22:06:16 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/video/2023/jul/26/sinead-oconnor-the-turbulent-career-of-the-irish-sensation-video-obituary" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/27/drone-footage-shows-aftermath-of-wildfires-on-2500-year-old-sicilian-temple-video" target="_blank">Drone footage shows aftermath of wildfires on 2,500-year-old Sicilian temple – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The temple of Segesta has been turned to ash after days of fires spreading across Sicily. The island has been devastated by wildfires that have killed at least three people. Heatwaves and severe storms have also affected the north of Italy, while heatwaves and storms hit the north.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:44:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/27/drone-footage-shows-aftermath-of-wildfires-on-2500-year-old-sicilian-temple-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/greece-wildfires-break-out-corfu-thousands-flee-rhodes-blazes-video-report" target="_blank">Greece: wildfires rage on three islands and mainland – video report - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Firefighters struggling to contain 82 wildfires across the country, 64 of which started on Sunday, the hottest day of the summer so far. As well as huge blazes on Rhodes, 19,000 people were forced to flee the island of Rhodes. Wildfires also broke out on Corfu, Corfu and in the northern Peloponnese region.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 13:09:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/greece-wildfires-break-out-corfu-thousands-flee-rhodes-blazes-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/spain-faces-political-gridlock-after-national-elections-video-report" target="_blank">Spain faces political gridlock after national elections – video report - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Spain appears to be heading for political gridlock after rightwing parties fail to clinch a decisive victory. Pro-independence Catalan and Basque parties as potential kingmakers. Conservative People's party will be given first attempt at trying to cobble together enough votes to win a prime-ministerial investiture vote.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 12:11:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/spain-faces-political-gridlock-after-national-elections-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather and adds a further spurt of warmth to an already overheating world.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Playing Out is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children’s doorsteps. Some experts say a growing mental and physical health crisis could be a result. Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian's Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet Playing Out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved millions of lives and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">What you need to know about the 'extreme' heatwave hitting our oceans – video explainer - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Sea temperatures, particularly off the north-east coast of England and west of Ireland, are several degrees above normal, breaking records for late spring and early summer. The Met Office has said that according to records dating to 1850, global sea surface temperatures in April and May reached an all-time high.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 14:22:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/24/tell-us-how-have-you-been-affected-by-wildfires-on-corfu" target="_blank">Greeks: tell us about the aftermath of the wildfires - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> We’d like to hear from local people about the impact of wildfires in regions including Rhodes, Magnesia, Corfu and Evia. Have you been affected? Have you had to evacuate? Has your home or business been damaged? We want to speak with local people on the situation where they are.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 10:03:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/24/tell-us-how-have-you-been-affected-by-wildfires-on-corfu" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/03/uk-workers-over-50-share-your-experience-of-being-a-food-courier" target="_blank">UK workers over 50: share your experience of being a food courier - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Work and pensions secretary, Mel Stride, made the comments during a visit to Deliveroo HQ. Deliveroo has recorded a 62% increase in riders aged over 50 since 2021. We're interested to hear from people aged 50 and over in the UK about what it’s like to work as couriers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 11:29:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/03/uk-workers-over-50-share-your-experience-of-being-a-food-courier" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/03/uk-film-and-tv-workers-how-are-hollywood-strikes-affecting-you" target="_blank">UK film and TV workers: how are Hollywood strikes affecting you? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> US actors’ union Sag-Aftra joined the Writers Guild of America (WGA) on strike over contract negotiations. Hollywood actors and writers have been on strike at the same time for over six decades. We want to hear how strikes are impacting the UK film and TV industry.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 16:12:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/03/uk-film-and-tv-workers-how-are-hollywood-strikes-affecting-you" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/26/people-in-turkey-and-syria-what-has-life-been-like-since-the-february-earthquakes" target="_blank">People in Turkey and Syria: what has life been like since the February earthquakes? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> We’d like to hear from people who were affected by the two devastating earthquakes of 7.8 and 7.6 magnitude on 6 February in Turkey and Syria. We want to know what their lives have been like since the disaster, and how their family and community have been affected.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 11:52:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/26/people-in-turkey-and-syria-what-has-life-been-like-since-the-february-earthquakes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/04/donald-trump-january-6-indictment-podcast" target="_blank">Donald Trump’s January 6 indictment - podcast - 